<p>The Seneca Creek and Great Seneca Highway corridors feature a mix of townhomes and single-family residences, where ground-mount solar systems may be viable alternatives to rooftop installations. Neighborhoods near the Germantown Town Center benefit from newer electrical infrastructure that simplifies solar interconnection processes. Throughout Germantown, homes built before 1990 typically see the greatest energy savings from combined solar and HVAC upgrades, as older systems often operate at much lower efficiency levels than current technologies.</p>

